## Key Design Decisions

### Ultra-Simple "3-Second Check" Design
1. Only 3 items by default: Wallet, Keys, Phone
2. Phone auto-checked (user obviously has their phone)
3. Giant 90px tap targets
4. "Got 'em all!" button for quick confirmation
5. Voice announcements for accessibility
6. Haptic feedback on each tap

### Smart Home Detection (Zero Setup)
- Tracks where phone charges overnight
- After 3+ overnight charges at same location = home
- Automatically starts geofence monitoring
- User never has to configure anything

### Morning Prep Items (Defaults)
Active by default:
- Wallet, Keys, Phone, Bag, Headphones, Medication, Water Bottle

Inactive (user can enable):
- Laptop, Charger, Glasses, ID Badge, Lunch, Umbrella, Jacket

### Location Checkout Items
Gym: Water bottle, Headphones, Towel, Gym bag, Phone, Keys
Work: Laptop/charger, Badge, Phone, Keys, Wallet, Headphones, Bag
Home: Wallet, Keys, Phone, Bag, Headphones
School: Backpack, Laptop, Homework, Phone, Lunch, Water bottle, Charger

